valid_ipN: Raise TypeError for non string value (#371)

This fixes the inconsistent behavior of valid_ipv4 and valid_ipv6 for
non-string value, and makes both these methods raise TypeError. These
returned False in <1.0.0 but that behavior was not intended.

Jakub's edit: the exceptions raised before came from the parsing
internals. These deliberate TypeErrors will make it more obvious
what's wrong.

commit.message:
Support running the interactive shell without IPython

While we can recommend it it doesn't seem worth it to *require* this
relatively heavy dependency.

Handle IP parsing errors more precisely

Reducing the amount of code in try blocks and catching only specific
exception types will both make the code easier to understand but also
stop hiding problems (see: IPv6 valid_str hiding TypeErrors before).

Improve the exceptions raised by fbsocket's inet_pton (#370)

The original socket.inet_pton raises TypeError on non-str passed as an
address and OSError in case of an invalid address.

This will help with more precise exception handling (we use
socket.inet_pton and fbsocket.inet_pton interchangeably in a couple of
places).
